==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*skot-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[skot]], Old Saxon [[silscot|sīlscot]], Old High German [[scoz]] (German [[Schoß]]), Old Norse [[skot]].  Compare [[scot]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʃe:ot/}}

===Noun===
{{Latinx|'''sceot'''}} {{n}} (plural same)

# [[shot]], act of shooting
# [[missile]], [[shot]]
# [[darting]], rapid movement

